  <Subject Subject_ID="300053451">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300053450</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>radiography [300053450], picture-taking techniques by radiation type [300053456], picture-taking techniques [300138790], photographic techniques [300134334], photography and photographic processes and techniques [300149146], image-making processes and techniques [300053159], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process that records the location and distribution in an object of radioactive substances, or those made radioactive in order to be detected, when radiation from these substances act on a photographic emulsion placed in close contact with the object. When used on a painting, identifies areas of pigments through elemental half lives.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Radiografie waarmee wordt vastgesteld waar en in welke mate radioactieve stoffen of stoffen die radioactief zijn gemaakt om te kunnen worden opgespoord, zich in een bepaald object bevinden, wanneer de straling die door deze stoffen wordt uitgezonden, inwerkt op een fotografische emulsie die in nauw contact staat met het object. Wanneer autoradiografie op een schilderij wordt toegepast, kan op grond van de halveringstijden de plaatsing van bepaalde pigmenten worden vastgesteld.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>透過放射性物質在置於物件旁的感光乳劑上起作用，記錄具備放射性物質或被賦予放射性物質之物件，其位置和散佈區域的過程。當使用於繪畫時，即可藉由元素的半衰期辨識出顏料。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
